WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.083 --> 00:00:04.083
Accessibility is a fundamental human
right recognised in Australia.

2
00:00:04.708 --> 00:00:08.125
It is also a responsibility
of the New South Wales Government.

3
00:00:08.791 --> 00:00:12.125
Accessibility is grounded
in international, Commonwealth

4
00:00:12.125 --> 00:00:13.958
and state laws.

5
00:00:13.958 --> 00:00:17.125
The Commonwealth Anti-Discrimination
Act and Disability

6
00:00:17.125 --> 00:00:21.125
Discrimination Act and the New South
Wales Disability Inclusion Act

7
00:00:21.750 --> 00:00:24.958
all mark milestones
towards inclusivity and equality.

8
00:00:25.750 --> 00:00:28.750
Australia is a signatory
of the UN Convention

9
00:00:28.750 --> 00:00:31.791
on the Rights of Persons
with Disabilities, committing us

10
00:00:31.791 --> 00:00:34.791
to making our work accessible
for people with disability.

11
00:00:35.250 --> 00:00:37.916
The Commonwealth Disability
Discrimination Act

12
00:00:37.916 --> 00:00:41.625
also states it's unlawful
to discriminate based on disability.

13
00:00:42.250 --> 00:00:46.125
Accessibility is a standard
guided by the Australian standard

14
00:00:46.125 --> 00:00:49.625
on accessibility and W3C web
guidelines.

15
00:00:49.875 --> 00:00:51.958
The New South Wales
Government strives

16
00:00:51.958 --> 00:00:55.041
to ensure accessible ICT products
and services.

17
00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:59.083
As New South Wales
Government staff, it's essential

18
00:00:59.083 --> 00:01:02.083
to consider accessibility
in your daily work tasks.

19
00:01:02.416 --> 00:01:03.250
Every cluster

20
00:01:03.250 --> 00:01:06.791
has its own New South Wales
Disability Inclusion Action Plan,

21
00:01:07.083 --> 00:01:10.250
and it is our obligation to ensure
that our digital products

22
00:01:10.250 --> 00:01:12.500
and services
are accessible to everyone.

